<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Learn -ISM/-IST pairs:</span> Every -ISM word has a matching -IST form: OPTIMISM/OPTIMIST, CRITICISM/CRITIC+IST, HEROISM/no direct pair. Knowing both gives you two bingo options from one root.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">M on premium squares:</span> M is worth 3 points — on a DLS it becomes 6, on TLS it becomes 9. Since -ISM ends with M, try to position the word so M lands on a premium tile for maximum value.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SCHISM as a power play:</span> At 13 points in just 6 letters (S+C+H+I+S+M), SCHISM is one of the most efficient short words in Scrabble. Both S tiles and the CH digraph make it achievable from common racks.</p>
  </div>
</div>

